inputs: Once upon a time, there was a dog named Spot. Spot had a red collar that he wore all the time. One day, Spot went outside to play. He ran and ran until he saw a bird in the sky. The bird was flying so fast, it looked like it was going to zoom away. Spot barked and chased after the bird. But then, he got too close and the bird flew away. Spot was sad and went back home. When he got home, his owner was there and gave him a treat. The owner noticed that Spot's collar was dirty and harsh. So, the owner took off the collar and cleaned it. Spot was happy again and wagged his tail.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a noisy jungle. The birds chirped loudly and the monkeys hollered from the trees. One day, a leopard came to the jungle. He was very big and had lots of spots. He roared loudly and scared all the animals.  The leopard was very hungry and wanted to eat something. He saw a little rabbit and chased it. The rabbit ran and ran, but the leopard was too fast. The leopard caught the rabbit and ate it all up.  The other animals wept and wept. They were sad that the leopard had eaten their friend. They wished the leopard had never come to their jungle. The end.

inputs: Once upon a time there was a girl who was very honest. Her name was Jane. Jane loved to help her parents and friends whenever she could but she had a problem. Every day, she kept insisting that she needed more help! Her mother and father thought she was just being silly but her friends soon realised that Jane was being honest. So they started to help her more and take on some of the jobs she was asking them to do. Jane was very pleased that her friends were being so helpful. inputs: Once, there was an ancient pond. In the middle of the pond was a big puddle. The puddle looked old and was very quiet. One day, a frog came out of the puddle and went around the pond. He wanted to find something to complete the ancient pond. The frog looked around the pond and found some stones, shells and small sticks. He gathered all these things together and began to make something. He carefully put the stones around the edge of the puddle and the shells and sticks around the stones. He smiled when he was done. inputs: Once upon a time, there was a girl named Lily. She had a boo-boo on her knee and it hurt a lot. Her mommy said she needed to be patient and wait for it to get better.  One day, Lily went to the park and saw a boy playing with a balloon. She wanted to play too, but she didn't have a balloon. The boy was very nice and decided to attach his balloon to Lily's wrist so she could play too.  Lily was so happy and grateful to the boy for being patient and kind. She played with the balloon and forgot all about her boo-boo knee. From that day on, Lily and the boy became good friends and played together often.

inputs: Once upon a time there was a big, strong bear. The bear had a nice cabin all by himself. He was always content in it. One day, the bear went on a walk in the woods. Suddenly, he heard a noise from a nearby bush. He went to investigate and saw a small rabbit complaining. "What's wrong?" asked the bear. "My home is too small," said the rabbit. The bear thought for a moment. "Would you like to live in my big cabin?" he asked. The rabbit's eyes lit up. "Yes!" The bear and the rabbit went back to the bear's cabin and the rabbit moved in. Since then, the bear and the rabbit have been very happy in their big cabin.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little bunny named Bun. Bun liked to dig in the dirt and find things to eat. One day, Bun found a big root! It was so big that Bun had to mix the dirt around it to get it out.  Bun was so happy with the root that he decided to share it with his friends. inputs: Once upon a time, there was a spider. The spider was very small and had eight legs. It wanted to lay its eggs, but it couldn't find a good spot. The spider looked and looked, but it was very persistent.  Finally, the spider found a cozy corner in the attic. It laid its eggs there and waited patiently. Soon, the eggs hatched into tiny spiders. The baby spiders were happy and crawled all around. The persistent spider was glad it found a good spot to lay its eggs.  From then on, the spider and its babies lived happily in the cozy corner of the attic. They would play and lay in the sun, and the persistent spider was always on the lookout for a good spot to lay more eggs. The end.

inputs: Once upon a time there was a lazy cat who loved pasta. He loved it so much that he would always try to zip into the kitchen whenever he thought no one was looking! One day, he got so excited that he accidentally zipped out of the window. He was lost and had no idea what to do. He saw some delicious looking pasta in the distance and he quickly zipped towards it. When he got there, he was surprised to discover it was a giant plate of delicious pasta, just for him! He was so happy that he gobbled it all up in a matter of minutes. The cat was so full and content that he zipped off home and had a nice long nap! The End.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little mole. The mole lived in a hole in the ground. One day, the mole wanted to jump out of the hole, but it was too high. The mole tried and tried, but it couldn't jump high enough. Then, the mole saw a bitter apple on the ground. The mole thought, "Maybe if I eat the bitter apple, I will be able to jump higher." So, the mole ate the bitter apple. After eating the bitter apple, the mole felt stronger. It jumped and jumped, and finally, it was able to jump out of the hole. The mole was so happy to be out of the hole and see the sunshine. From then on, the mole ate bitter apples every day and became the best jumper in the whole forest.

It made the people clap with happiness. Soon the sail was moving faster and faster. All around the sail people were clapping, jumping and yelling with joy. Then the sail stopped. Everyone became quiet and the sail became still again. The people clapped once more, and the sun started to set.  It was a magical day - the calm sail had taken them on a wonderful adventure.
labels: 從前有塊大藍色的帆，安靜地躺在那兒。然後，神奇的事發生了 — 帆開始動起來！它上上下下，左左右右地動著，讓人高興得拍手。很快，帆動得更快，周圍的人也更興奮，他們拍手、跳躍、大喊著，盡情享受這歡樂的時刻。然後，帆停了下來。大家安靜下來，帆也再次靜止。人們再次拍手，太陽也開始落山。這真是一個神奇的日子 — 這塊平靜的帆帶他們經歷了一場精彩的冒險。

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She was very eager to go to the theater to watch a play. Her mommy and daddy baked some cookies for her to take to the theater.  Lily was very happy and hugged her mommy and daddy. She put the cookies in a bag and they all went to the theater. When they got there, Lily saw many people waiting in line to go inside. She was very happy and thanked her mommy and daddy for taking her to the theater.

inputs: Once upon a time there was a strong man. He laughed all day long.  One day, he found a special ornament. He held it tight in his hand and laughed even louder. He was so happy to own an ornament so beautiful.  He held it up to the sun and the sparkles made him laugh even harder. He laughed until his sides hurt. He took the ornament everywhere with him. He was so proud and laughed every time he looked at it. But one day, a gust of wind came and blew the ornament away. He laughed because it was a funny sight, watching the ornament fly away.  He ran after it, but he could not catch it. Instead, he laughed and said goodbye. He knew that the ornament had a grand adventure to go on.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a fish named Nemo. Nemo was swimming in the ocean when he saw a hook. He knew that the hook was not good for him, so he swam away.  One day, Nemo got caught on the hook. He was scared and couldn't move. Luckily, a kind fish saw him and helped him. The kind fish pulled the hook out of Nemo's mouth and let him go back into the water.  Nemo was so happy to be free again. He thanked the kind fish and promised to never be selfish again. inputs: Once upon a time there was a big, bright net. It was hung between two tall trees in a sunny park. One day, a little black bird was flying in the park when it got caught in the net! The bird panicked and started to flutter around, but it just could not get away. Just then, a friendly bear came walking along. He saw the poor bird struggling and immediately knew what to do. He carefully pulled the net away from the trees and the bird flew up in the air and away. The bird was so happy and flew off to find a new place to make its home. The bear smiled as he watched the bird fly away and waved goodbye. The end.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lucy. She loved to travel and explore the world. Today, she was on her way to a new place and was very excited. At the station, Lucy went to the ticket counter to get her ticket. The nice man behind the counter gave her a little ticket and told her to get on the train. Lucy got on the train and found a seat. There were boxes and packages all around her. Then she heard a loud noise. It was the train conductor, asking everyone to load the luggage onto the train. So Lucy got up and helped the others put their bags on the train. Soon the train was loaded, and they were ready to go! Lucy waved goodbye to everyone at the station and settled into her seat. He cuddled up next to the fence and was soon sound asleep. The sun shone brightly and the bear woke up. He saw a very tall metal tower. He thought it looked very fun and he wanted to join it. He jumped up and climbed up the tower. Soon, the bear was at the top. He sat at the top of the tower and looked around. He could see many things like trees and houses. But he was tired after all the climbing and so he decided to take a nap. When the bear woke up, he clambered back down the tower. He had had a lot of fun joining the tower. He was a little tired after his adventures, but he was happy.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a girl named Lucy. Lucy liked to play dress-up with her mommy's makeup. She would get all dressed up and put on lipstick and blush.  One day, Lucy's mommy told her that it's important to be modest when wearing makeup. That means not putting too much on and looking natural. Lucy didn't understand at first, but her mommy showed her how to use just a little bit of makeup to make her cheeks rosy and her lips pink. From then on, Lucy always made sure to be modest with her makeup. She would get ready for the day by putting on just a little bit of lipstick and blush, and she looked beautiful. Her mommy was proud of her for being so grown-up and responsible. The end.

inputs: John lay on the grass and looked up at the big, blue sky. He was feeling so very hungry. Suddenly he heard laughing and cheering. He saw a big group of children playing with a football. John jumped up and ran over to join them. The children welcomed John and before he knew it he was joining in the fun, kicking the football as hard as he could. John felt so happy playing with the children. He ran and ran and ran and by the time he stopped he was no longer hungry. All the running had taken away his hunger. John lay down on the grass again and smiled up at the sky. He was so happy that he had made such good friends and found something he loved doing - playing football was lots of fun!

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little bear who wanted to succeed. He was very determined but things kept going wrong. One day, he found a dull bottle in the woods. He thought it might help him. He wished and wished, but nothing happened. He held the bottle tight and was about to give up when suddenly a magical sparkle came out of the bottle! He was so excited. inputs: Once there was a rich pumpkin. It was the biggest and most beautiful pumpkin that had ever been seen. Everyday, the pumpkin wanted to be turned into something special. So everyday the pumpkin would look down at the ground and pray. It prayed that it would become something great. One day, the farmer heard the pumpkin's prayers and he decided to turn it into a pie. He took it to the kitchen and put it in the oven, and all day long it smelled of pumpkin. Finally, the farmer took it out of the oven and presented it to the family. inputs: Once there was an oak tree in a meadow. One day, it was a cold day and the oak tree felt very chilly. Then, all of a sudden, the oak tree saw a bright light and started to burn. The flames reached up to the sky and lit up the meadow. Everyone who saw it was very scared and ran away.  The fire turned the oak tree into ashes and soon the meadow was very dark. But then, something amazing happened. The next day, when the sky was bright and cold again, a new oak tree sprouted from the ashes of the old one. It was happy and strong. inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little boy. He had a wallet, which was very special to him. He liked to carry it with him everywhere. One day, the little boy went out and he accidentaly dropped his wallet in a muddy puddle. The wallet was covered in mud and wet. But the little boy didn't give up. He wiped the wallet off with his hands to make it clean again. The wallet wasn't as clean as it used to be, but the little boy liked it even more because of the long time it took him to wipe it off. The little boy learnt a valuable lesson that day: never give up, even when something takes a long time. With a bit of determination, you can achieve great things.

inputs: Onceupon a time, there was a scared sailor. He was trembling in the night. He wanted to find help, but didn't know where to turn. Suddenly, he heard a voice counting from far away. He followed the voice and came to a beach. There was a small child there counting starfish. The sailor was relieved and asked the child to help him. The child gladly agreed and they set off together. As they walked, the child pointed out things, counting as they went. The sailor was surprised by all the numbers the child knew. Soon they arrived at the sailor's home and he thanked the child for his help. The child smiled and left, counting the pebbles on the path as he went.

inputs: Today, a white rabbit was hopping along. It found some food, berries, and scattered them near its hole. It wanted to save some food for later. The white rabbit was so happy; it hopped and hopped in circles. The rabbit found some more food, a few nuts, and it scattered them away, far away from its home. It then hopped to a different place and scattered some more food. The rabbit was very busy today. When night came, the rabbit scampered back to its home. inputs: One day a small pig was walking around in the woods. The pig saw something and he was very curious. So he went a bit closer and he saw a big black spider. The pig was scared, but he was brave. He decided to stay and watch the spider. The spider looked back at the pig and the pig jumped. Then the spider moved closer and the pig felt a bit scared. But he stayed still. The spider got closer and closer and the pig started to get really scared. The spider was about to bite the pig. But before it could, something made a noise in the woods. The spider ran away, scared. The pig was relieved and he was very happy. He knew that he had been very brave and that the noise had saved him from being bitten.

inputs: Once upon a time there was a little girl who went for a walk. As she was walking, she saw something on the ground. She went closer to have a look and discovered it was a broken salad bowl. She was surprised because she didn't expect to find a salad bowl in the middle of the grass! The little girl picked up the broken bowl and saw some pieces of salad inside. She tasted the salad and it was delicious! She was so happy because she was hungry and now she had something to eat. She looked around and saw a broken branch. She took the branch and put some of the salad in the branch. Then she had fun giving some of the salad to the birds and animals she saw. After she was done, she was full! She discovered how fun it is to explore and to discover new things!

The box had a note on it. The note said, "Release the candy inside." Tim was so happy. He opened the box and found lots and lots of candy. Tim shared the candy with his friends. They all ate candy and played together. Tim was very happy. He learned that sharing made everyone happy. And they all lived happily ever after.

inputs: Once upon a time, in a big green forest, there lived a little leaf. The little leaf loved to talk to all the animals and trees. Every day, the leaf would chat with his friends, the birds, the bugs, and the squirrels. One day, a heavy rain came to the forest. The little leaf was scared. The wind blew hard, and the rain was so heavy that the leaf could not talk to his friends. The little leaf felt sad and lonely. After the rain stopped, the sun came out and the forest was happy again. The little leaf could talk to his friends again. They all laughed and played together. The little leaf was no longer sad, and the heavy rain was just a memory.

inputs: Once there was a little girl who lived in the forest. One day, she wanted to sort her toys. On her way, she saw a wolf. She felt scared and started to cry. The wolf noticed her and said "Don't be afraid, I'm here to help you." The girl didn't understand why the wolf wanted to help but decided to trust him. She asked the wolf to help her sort her toys. The wolf said "I know a lot of things, but sorting toys is not one of them. I'm an ignorant wolf, I'm sorry." The girl smiled and said "It's OK, I can do it myself." labels: 以前有個小女孩喺森林度生活。有一日，佢想整理啲玩具。佢行緊路嘅時候，見到隻狼。佢好驚，開始喊。隻狼見到佢，就話：「唔好驚，我係嚟幫你嘅。」個女孩唔明點解隻狼想幫手，但係決定信佢。佢搵隻狼幫手整玩具。隻狼話：「我識好多嘢，但係整玩具就唔係其中一樣。我係隻無知嘅狼，對唔住。」個女孩笑咗笑，話：「無問題，我自己整得嚟。」所以佢花時間整好啲玩具。佢很快就整好咗，多謝隻狼想幫手。隻狼走嗰陣，感覺快樂同自豪。

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a rich family who had a big, comfy mattress. Every night they would all pile on top of it and tell stories. But the mattress was getting old, and it wasn't very strong. One night, it suddenly split in two!  The family was very surprised. One of the younger children, who was only three years old, began to cry.  "Why did it split?" the child asked between sobs. His father smiled and said, "It split because it was old and it just couldn't hold us all anymore."  The child smiled, and everyone helped to patch up the mattress so it wouldn't split next time. And from then on, everyone made sure not to put too many people on the mattress!

inputs: Once upon a time there was a mighty dragon. He wanted to travel, so he packed his things and zoomed off. The dragon flew faster than the clouds and whizzed past the trees and buildings. After a while, the dragon arrived at a very magical place. In front of him was a big, shiny fridge. The dragon was very excited and he ran over to it. The fridge had a very big door and inside it were all sorts of yummy things.  The dragon grabbed a few treats and stuffed them in his bag. inputs: One day, Lisa and her mom went to the park. They brought a big potato. It was very fine. They paused for a moment and looked around. There were so many things to explore. Lisa spotted a tall tree and pointed at it. Her mom smiled and said that they should climb the tree! Lisa was excited! She grabbed the potato and started to climb. Her mom followed her and together they reached the tallest branch.  The view was magnificent. Lisa looked over the park and paused for a few moments. She could see the sun setting and the sky turning orange. Then it was time to go home. Lisa and her mom climbed down the tree, took the fine potato and headed home.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little cat. The cat was very tired. It would yawn all day long. One day, the cat wanted to learn a new word. It thought that if it knew a new word, it would feel alert and not yawn so much. The cat asked its friend, the dog, for help. The dog knew many words. The dog taught the cat a new word. The new word was "play". The cat liked the word "play" a lot. It made the cat feel happy and alert. The cat and the dog played together every day. They would run, jump, and laugh. inputs: Once upon a time, there was a wise owl who lived in a tree. Every Tuesday, the owl would fly to the river to catch fish for dinner. But one day, it started to rain and the owl got wet. So, the owl flew back to its tree to dry itself off.  The owl flapped its wings and shook its feathers to get dry. After a while, the sun came out and the owl felt warm again. It decided to wait until next Tuesday to catch fish. From then on, the owl always checked the weather before going out to catch fish.

inputs: Sara loved to visit her grandma on the farm. She liked to see the animals and help with the chores. Her favorite animal was the horse. His name was Brownie and he was big and strong and cheerful. He liked to run and jump and neigh. One day, Sara and her grandma made some bread and jam for lunch. Sara wanted to share some with Brownie. She took a slice of bread and spread some jam on it. She wrapped it in a napkin and ran to the barn. She found Brownie in his stall and gave him a hug. "Hello, Brownie," she said. "I have a treat for you. Do you want some bread and jam?" Brownie nodded and snorted. He took the bread from Sara's hand and ate it in one bite. He licked his lips and nuzzled Sara's cheek. He was happy and grateful. "Thank you, Sara," he said in his horse way. "That was yummy. You are very kind." Sara smiled and stroked his mane. She felt happy and proud. "You're welcome, Brownie," she said. "You are my best friend. I love you." They hugged and played for a while. So he opened the fridge and saw lots of bottles and cans inside, but they were all very warm.  John thought for a moment. Then he remembered he needed to freeze it.  He said to his friend, "We need to make the drinks cold. Can you help me put them in the freezer?"  His friend smiled and said, "Yes, that's easy. Let's put them in there now." inputs: Once there was a twig. It was an amazing twig. The twig wanted to explore the world. So one day, the twig dropped from the tree. It fell and fell and felt the wind on its branches.  The twig landed in a puddle. The twig was so excited to splash in the puddle. As the twig swished around, it saw all sorts of wonderful things. The twig saw a butterfly, a frog, and an ant.  The twig danced and spun around in the puddle. It was so fun that the twig didn't want to leave. But eventually, the twig said goodbye to its friends and dropped to the ground.  The twig made its way back to the tree and laughed about the amazing things it saw. From then on, the twig was never afraid to drop from the tree and explore.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a girl named Lucy. Lucy loved to play outside in the sun. One day, the weather was not regular. It was raining a lot. Lucy was sad because she could not play outside. Lucy's mom saw her sad face. She wanted to help Lucy feel better. So, she provided a big umbrella. Lucy took the umbrella and went outside. She jumped in the puddles and laughed. The rain did not make her sad anymore. After a while, the rain stopped and the sun came out. Lucy saw a big rainbow in the sky. She was very happy. She knew that even when the weather was not regular, she could still have fun.

She was so wet that she could squeeze the water right out of her clothes. When she got home, she was exhausted. She changed out of her wet clothes and put her toys away. She was so proud of herself for keeping her bedroom so tidy!

inputs: Once upon a time there was a happy little child. The child's name was Abigail and she was three years old. Every day Abigail would go out to play in the park.  One day Abigail was at the park with her mother and her pet dog. Abigail was running around, playing tag with her dog. Suddenly, Abigail heard her mother calling her name. "Abigail, it's time to go home," her mother said. Abigail was sad because she wanted to stay and play longer. Her mother asked her if she remembered the slow walk rule. inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play outside in the bright sun. One day, Timmy found a screw on the ground. He picked it up and looked at it closely. Suddenly, a big dog came running towards Timmy. The dog opened his mouth wide and tried to bite Timmy. But Timmy was quick and he threw the screw at the dog. The screw hit the dog's nose and the dog ran away. Timmy felt very proud of himself for being brave. From that day on, Timmy always carried a screw with him, just in case he needed to scare away any more dogs.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little bird. The bird was very sad because she was all alone. She felt lonely and wished she had a friend to play with.  One day, a kind rabbit passed by and saw the little bird sitting by herself. The rabbit asked, "Why are you so sad?" The bird replied, "I am lonely and have no one to play with."  The rabbit felt sorry for the little bird and said, "Don't worry, I will be your friend. We can play together and have lots of fun." The bird was very happy and thanked the rabbit.  From that day on, the little bird and the rabbit played together every day. They had so much fun and the bird was no longer lonely. She was grateful to have a friend like the rabbit.

inputs: Once upon a time, there was a little girl who wanted to ride her bike. She looked out the window and saw cherry trees growing all around. She was so excited that she quickly jumped onto her bike and began to ride. She rode around and around, finding joy in the wind blowing through her hair. The cherry trees were so beautiful that the little girl wanted to pick some. She stopped to pick a few big red cherries, then rode away. She went around and around, feeling so happy as she rode. But soon, the little girl started to feel lonely. She looked around and realized she was all alone. The lonely little girl rode far away from the cherry trees. The bird was so scared that he closed his eyes. He tried to stay as still as possible. When the shaking stopped, the bird opened his eyes again and looked around.
